against the Queen his Sovereign Lady. If then his
Purpose so were to pursue it with force, it must
needs follow, that the same must be of Intent,
Imagination, and Compassing, to deprive and
depose the Queen's Majesty from her Crown, Royal
Estate, and Dignity, and to advance and maintain
that false and usurp'd Title of the (^Scotish^) Queen unto
the present possession of the Crown of (^England^) , and
so consequently, for maintenance of his
Imagination and Purpose, to compass the Queen's Majesty's
Death and Destruction. Now shall you further
hear Proof of his own words, declaring the same
intent to pursue the Marriage by force, and rather
to lose his Life than to give it over.
