   [$ (^Duke.^) $] It may be that (^Barker^) received this Letter
as you spake of, and that (^Gutbert^) decyphered it,
and that it contain'd the Matters that you alledge;
it may be that they kept that Letter still to
themselves, and might bring me another Letter,
containing only such Matter as I was contented with,
containing the private Cause.
   [$ (^Sollic.^) $] An unlikely matter; but thus you see the
Duke confesseth the receipt of the Letter, he only
